{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771324109,"nonce":"sjko11W/n12nWmX+sBKT/ZwmzZk=","title":"Item-department binding: unclear how items are assigned to departments","message":"Items (ParentItem/Item) appear to be bound to a department, but there is no UI to set or change which department an item belongs to. It seems items are implicitly assigned to whatever department the user is currently in when the item is created.\n\nQuestions to investigate:\n- How is the item-department relationship established? Is it set at creation time based on the user's current department?\n- Can items be moved between departments?\n- Should there be an explicit department selector when creating/editing items?\n- What happens to items when a user switches departments - do they only see items from their current department?","files":null}]}